<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-2B68DA63-419E-4537-A2C3-B73B9C4F3C1C" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-2B68DA63-419E-4537-A2C3-B73B9C4F3C1C" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title "> How to upgrade from CMYK to CMYK-W</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-0E3E2CA2-5349-4FAF-80F5-347AA9765351"><p class="- topic/p "> This document gives an overview of the white ink upgrade procedure, both for M3 and M5, towards M3W and M5W. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Installation</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-4EBEF3C5-5032-4424-B092-74A3938DD840" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> Required time</title><p class="- topic/p "> The upgrade will take approximately 3 - 3,5 hours. 
</p></section><prereq id="GUID-F8EE43B1-36AF-4F86-8810-3B686A03AF19" class="- topic/section task/prereq "><ul id="UL_B1463683E2BA49668D370C3F7729CCCB" class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> If the waste tray is above 60% you need to preventively replace the waste tray by an empty one.
</p></li><li id="LI_57D0F61FB24A4B47AAF99D88FCD26D56" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Place the top cover in the service position. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See 
<xref keyref="24DISA060" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-120956FD-BCBD-4084-9823-BCEEFB44C508.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 24 How to place the top cover in the service position?>24 How to place the top cover in the service position</xref> 
</p></li></ul></prereq><section id="GUID-E4895B67-7FC1-4974-A5C8-D34725505879" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Required tools</title><ul id="UL_CEA4CD427612471CA3540AD5430B21C2" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_B007BBFF5E5743C89A24651737F64808" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">1 unused Printhead
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Screwdriver Torx T10 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Antistatic wrist strap 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Protective gloves: 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Microflex 
</b> 93-260 gloves 
</p></li><li id="LI_856CDDC7431149C9B79FD5C51D21B2AC" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Flex Cable for connecting printhead to carriage PBA (part of printer installation material). 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Grease for the pumptube.
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> ILMS license "Colorado M-series License White" or "Upgrade License White" 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-C02D66D1-E3CC-4BC2-95F8-775D93D93431" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Warning / Caution</title><note type="caution" id="GUID-A97040BC-F110-4E4B-9CFF-E8082B9DA00E" class="- topic/note "><fig id="GUID-2D7D94A0-B26C-4C0B-B6A3-20C8621663A2" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Avoid skin contact with ink: wear protective gloves. 
</p><fig id="GUID-7C716739-2AD7-42F8-8EF6-B28A8E7B1F76" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> Protect your eyes from splashing ink: wear safety glasses. 
</p></note><note type="important" id="GUID-19212FE1-0739-4D36-AE4D-49667AC5A182" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Use an antistatic wrist strap. 
</p></note></section><section id="GUID-EC9C24D5-D455-4022-B616-D7FEF4DE0A1A" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Illustration</title><fig id="GUID-2C64F110-689D-49EB-83D5-DD92BB421A3D" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-B921C2E4-0490-4533-AAEC-FBC75CA76CE6-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-B921C2E4-0490-4533-AAEC-FBC75CA76CE6-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="SECTION_83EFA574E57B4B64A0DD595529E957E2" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> Execute the upgrade</title></section><section id="GUID-B79CFD47-BC2F-483C-B882-4523128912A1" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Prepare the ink system for white ink</title><table pgwide="1" id="GUID-A1283AB6-0A99-427B-92F3-9F14FC91D2DD" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the knife compartment cover. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See: 
<xref keyref="24DISA034" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-1D8187CA-1F3B-4EBF-9E0A-F130AF910D4A.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 24 How to remove the knife compartment cover?>24 How to remove the knife compartment cover</xref> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Remove the cover below the cover of the knife compartment. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> See: 
<xref keyref="24DISA032" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-704C0C6B-5CA9-4D4D-B8A9-6C1132D65581.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 24 How to remove the cover below the cover of the knife...?>24 How to remove the cover below the cover of the knife compartment</xref> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the media input right cover. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See: 
<xref keyref="24DISA022" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-A1586343-23C1-47B2-BE4B-BB8972057671.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 24 How to remove the media input right cover?>24 How to remove the media input right cover</xref> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Open the ink system. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> See: 
<xref keyref="02DISA012" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-1C874C66-3A17-4AC4-886B-753A1A37D196.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 02 Open the ink system?>02 Open the ink system</xref> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the rear top cover of the ink system . 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See: 
<xref keyref="02DISA014" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-44A21941-A21F-4C37-A066-3CEA7BE54DAA.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 02 How to remove the rear top cover of the ink system...?>02 How to remove the rear top cover of the ink system</xref> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Install and grease the pump for white only 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See: 
<xref keyref="02install_pump_tubes_002" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-87BCE552-1B5E-4609-B104-F83697F46FF3.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 02 How to install and grease the pump tubes?>02 How to install and grease the pump tubes</xref> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-234D70A5-41EC-40E2-9E43-4217D346F540" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Install the white printhead</title><table id="GUID-BDB87D50-9E70-4086-AC9E-FA7970C76B0D" pgwide="1" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the shield (for stray light prevention). 
</p><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Loosen the 4 screws (T10) . 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Lift and remove the shield. 
</p></li></ol></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p><fig id="GUID-A2BB8070-635D-473F-B4EC-64E36FD41D3B" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-EFE9D7BE-04DE-44DE-A836-70DAF4F7CE84-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-EFE9D7BE-04DE-44DE-A836-70DAF4F7CE84-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Loosen the 4 screws and remove the bracket to the top. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-EA676652-7CD3-49C3-9F6A-B4DBD0B21435" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-B1F9523E-EA27-4B4B-83FA-40E36B669589-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-B1F9523E-EA27-4B4B-83FA-40E36B669589-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-2466871F-A493-410C-9FFB-8746D3E4A472" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-C9341357-2206-44A4-AA3A-EE917F4211E4-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-C9341357-2206-44A4-AA3A-EE917F4211E4-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-3282DEC0-0284-4AA7-968C-516EB12E335E" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-737DA8FE-BDDF-4BAA-9D02-6EF7764F508B-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-737DA8FE-BDDF-4BAA-9D02-6EF7764F508B-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the screw and the bracket. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-CA28E213-8DC6-41CF-801A-262CD0E0EFBE" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-93E0944A-2C39-428C-858E-D30F099B495F-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-93E0944A-2C39-428C-858E-D30F099B495F-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Loosen</b> the 2 screws (Torx T10) of the air duct. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-6831F5C9-23EA-4B31-9289-00B90ECEB95B" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-755046C7-E6D0-433A-9EF3-CF1C537793D3-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-755046C7-E6D0-433A-9EF3-CF1C537793D3-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Pull at the air duct: a gap is created between the sponge and the printheads. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-EB9250E5-606C-4051-849D-2738537282D1" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-6EFDFBE8-1003-4EEC-A3F5-92DC39F63759-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-6EFDFBE8-1003-4EEC-A3F5-92DC39F63759-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Unlock (squeeze and rotate) the printhead locking handle. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Push the locking handle till the end: positioned in a secured position. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-08F9E1B4-DE55-4689-9ADF-1CF0F7C4CDED" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-08667A32-DDD3-4A6A-96D8-2284047EFCF7-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-08667A32-DDD3-4A6A-96D8-2284047EFCF7-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-F12696FE-7495-472F-811B-C9D22DCA05DB" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-F3D25BC5-1234-414B-B59D-F505BF5D622B-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-F3D25BC5-1234-414B-B59D-F505BF5D622B-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">7 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Slide out the dummy printhead at position 1. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Store the dummy printhead within the printer at the installation parts. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Take the pre-folded flex cable you need to connect the White printhead. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The pre-folded flex cable is stored within the printer at the installation parts. 
</p></li></ol></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-25125833-9C3C-4B57-A2FA-E9C3D53CD8F6" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-21ED1D40-41B9-46F8-A3D1-86F01CA97D46-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-21ED1D40-41B9-46F8-A3D1-86F01CA97D46-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">8 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the “Plug Air Duct” from the air duct of position 1. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Put it in the plastic bag in the service box 
</p><fig id="GUID-BEED275B-E700-403A-895A-0FBC235D371B" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-06440A38-EADF-47AF-A550-7C21CB34E7E1-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-06440A38-EADF-47AF-A550-7C21CB34E7E1-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-CC1FC8E1-DDBE-4207-99AF-5A01D4C1AC61" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-5838FB4E-BAE0-497C-81D4-52AA3907CDDC-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-5838FB4E-BAE0-497C-81D4-52AA3907CDDC-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">9 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Take the printhead from the blister. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the green protection cover 
</p></li></ol></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-AD59F6C3-351E-4C07-A15C-F757610E3A6D" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-EA9E3038-E30D-4C02-AF7A-EFF89A5DE8D6-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-EA9E3038-E30D-4C02-AF7A-EFF89A5DE8D6-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">10 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Connect the pre-folded flex cable to the printhead. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-C13D1417-FC08-4E18-8295-5E743BEBFBE9" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-C7889529-253B-415E-930B-6BE64D65EFCC-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-C7889529-253B-415E-930B-6BE64D65EFCC-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">11 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Place/Slide the printhead at position 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">1</b> (at the right-hand side of the printhead carriage). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Check the position of the positioning balls in the matrix plate. 
</p><note id="GUID-959BFBB4-D50F-4726-9879-AF3F183F30FC" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">The numbers of the printheads are also indicated on the Carriage PBA (05PBA07). 
</p><fig id="FIG_0B24BF8D199746BF804369F01DDFF4FC" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-7C3E3996-24B1-46EE-B76A-A5D255689FD8-low.png" id="IMAGE_80FEBA485E634E6BAFE306E3357A365B" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-7C3E3996-24B1-46EE-B76A-A5D255689FD8-low.png"/></fig></note></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-AE0D796B-28B5-4153-B943-A487BB8F18B0" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-4AE00996-BCE7-4ACD-9D2D-E83C2130F0B4-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-4AE00996-BCE7-4ACD-9D2D-E83C2130F0B4-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">12 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Connect the flex cable to the Carriage PBA (05PBA07) at positions 1. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-B77BCA37-598A-44C8-911A-2008C5EADBA6" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-9601FA13-6017-4914-83F9-4F40E3B9086F-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-9601FA13-6017-4914-83F9-4F40E3B9086F-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">13 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Remove the red caps from the 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">air tubes</b>: 
</p><ul id="UL_0665D1761B8545CE88137ACC58F502CD" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_C57782D225224819B8BBEC4403AD5EAC" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> One at the carriage side. 
</p></li><li id="LI_B1A48A81DEC742B0A7477C756393CA56" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> One at the printhead side. 
</p></li></ul></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Connect the air tube to the filter. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Put the red caps in a plastic bag in the service box. 
</p></li></ol></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-2983F292-B92C-4EEB-826A-2B928B26AEF1" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-510FDDE3-6710-4E3D-ACDD-E9C8E24F916F-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-510FDDE3-6710-4E3D-ACDD-E9C8E24F916F-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-9E397D5C-43CB-4F79-A548-5DAE89651817" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-7E1A417C-DF02-4EAC-8645-EF6F9AF60189-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-7E1A417C-DF02-4EAC-8645-EF6F9AF60189-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">14 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Open the clamp of the air tube. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Squeeze the air tubes to protect that the tube sticks together. 
</p></li></ol></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-9079C7AC-FD58-4E60-B645-F798B314B077" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-C40804D0-6897-4093-84A9-66149D3620E8-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-C40804D0-6897-4093-84A9-66149D3620E8-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-D7465BE8-A275-40C4-B784-E93B92AD3C5F" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-BF2F240A-442A-4100-9979-8C7A6FCEE2E1-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-BF2F240A-442A-4100-9979-8C7A6FCEE2E1-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">15 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Remove the red caps from the 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">ink tubes</b>: 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Connect the white ink tube to the printhead in the carriage on position 1. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Put the red caps in a plastic bag in the service box. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Place the connected tubes back in the clamp of the printhead carriage. 
</p></li></ol></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-B5ECB98C-4BBE-4727-8A91-00D9E563C222" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-C8EE548C-8C2B-42F3-AB2E-867E66923636-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-C8EE548C-8C2B-42F3-AB2E-867E66923636-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">16 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Open (= rotate to vertical position) the 2 ink valves. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-0C009E1E-FEDE-49F4-8D1F-447015357207" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-88BDCE74-29FA-4A63-A190-22B9A5ABF9FB-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-88BDCE74-29FA-4A63-A190-22B9A5ABF9FB-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">17 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Check visually if all 5 printheads and 3 dummy printheads are in-line and the spring is on-top of the printhead hooks. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-F2132B14-AFD3-40C1-9E99-7E0EEAB0C500" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-17EA8842-563A-4F97-BD86-BE8981CCBEBC-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-17EA8842-563A-4F97-BD86-BE8981CCBEBC-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">18 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Close the printhead locking handle. 
</p><note id="GUID-C8EC0951-47D1-46C9-8C83-E46486577F0E" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Make sure the handle does not touch the screw. Position it beside the screw. 
</p></note></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-07D307A8-267B-4CBF-A0DD-6F80714C7FCD" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-181CD0AD-A04A-4F54-B6B8-B35B2B599389-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-181CD0AD-A04A-4F54-B6B8-B35B2B599389-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">19 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check the positions of the 5 printheads and 3 dummy printheads: 
</p><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Move the printhead carriage manually above the manual maintenance position. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Check the position of each printhead. Use a cell phone. 
</p><note type="important" id="GUID-384F0761-4CB0-4B86-835E-5DF4C2E6A6C1" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">If it is dark don't use LED or UV lamps. 
</p></note></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">If needed adapt the position. 
</p></li></ol></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-5B30ED33-48B1-411E-9287-B2C9DB2FAE20" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-8780E24D-2AC8-4807-B6AA-9F4DDACC0C37-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-8780E24D-2AC8-4807-B6AA-9F4DDACC0C37-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-58BCDF72-700C-4CE6-B388-8A37B0AA2DE0" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-EE1715F8-8A39-4D05-A43D-8DB1E85B29FC-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-EE1715F8-8A39-4D05-A43D-8DB1E85B29FC-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-88172780-D476-4A94-AA26-51279CEA2790" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-30D6C0D8-099E-4611-A495-7D97A78908F0-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-30D6C0D8-099E-4611-A495-7D97A78908F0-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">20 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Push the air duct in the direction of the printheads. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Lock the air duct with 2 screws (T10). 
</p></li></ol></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-40978937-3C1D-4049-ADC5-49A2CF9FB33F" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-4632A651-91FF-40E6-B581-116923012A0D-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-4632A651-91FF-40E6-B581-116923012A0D-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-B5DFE33E-84D0-4EB5-BA94-1BB9718662C2" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-475403F9-6304-4385-A5BC-A87695659BF3-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-475403F9-6304-4385-A5BC-A87695659BF3-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">21 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Install the bracket and lock it with 1 screw. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-0A5CE9A5-A29D-4EEB-9692-643AECA0D180" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-43D193E0-DA14-4162-BC59-EDEB83940819-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-43D193E0-DA14-4162-BC59-EDEB83940819-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">22 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Place the locking bracket and lock it with 4 screws. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-BB272C15-29C7-4B9F-805C-93364E070C8F" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-2BFF2814-334F-435E-B535-A162AF97121B-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-2BFF2814-334F-435E-B535-A162AF97121B-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">23 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Result: 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Assembled printhead carriage including 5 printheads. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-3D88242B-C5FF-446C-8071-2F6D42F7A569" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-9C7D4E63-057E-4C50-B753-3AA5A8854BEE-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-9C7D4E63-057E-4C50-B753-3AA5A8854BEE-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">24 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check: 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Double check all 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">ink tube connections</b> if they are properly connected. Make sure the ink tubes are not interchanged or do cross each other. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-DEB05460-811F-417B-8CE3-C61C7212C4ED" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-4CB5FA18-6C61-4C0E-B158-9A7DF21DE594-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-4CB5FA18-6C61-4C0E-B158-9A7DF21DE594-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-59A11931-1D25-4A46-9459-DC1014A27BC2" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-E320064B-7750-44C2-8140-E362F70520D2-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-E320064B-7750-44C2-8140-E362F70520D2-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">25 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check: 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Double check all 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">air tube connections</b>. Clamps need to be opened. Make sure the air tubes are not interchanged or do cross each other. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-B94A8CA0-CB34-4879-8053-8CA21302BA03" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-B91D974C-B31A-4B45-A001-CD8C59D5C2D7-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-B91D974C-B31A-4B45-A001-CD8C59D5C2D7-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">26 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check: 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Double check all 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">flex cable connections</b>. Make sure the flex cables are not interchanged or do cross each other. Check if the connectors are completely pressed in. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-FA503DDF-4F4F-412E-A165-2FCE83796787" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-566BE0D4-D5C5-4415-99F0-ADCBFAD44D6A-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-566BE0D4-D5C5-4415-99F0-ADCBFAD44D6A-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">27 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Keep the empty blisters of the printheads with the system. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Store them below the media drawer. 
</p></li></ol></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">28 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Install the shield (for stray light prevention). 
</p><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Fasten the 4 screws (T10) . 
</p></li></ol></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-DAA0E42F-4240-4907-817D-03928647FFF6" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-83491D84-D7D7-4EC5-9DD3-D25C4F5B3606-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-83491D84-D7D7-4EC5-9DD3-D25C4F5B3606-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-608C11BA-59F7-4F23-A19C-B59F43A80C03" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> Finialize the white ink upgrade</title><table id="GUID-3AEC3D31-5E94-4912-BAC4-25424972AAA8" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Follow the steps from SDS task “Upgrade White” 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">see: 
<xref keyref="TSKupgwhite" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-9806A531-8172-427C-A0B4-5DBC97FA13B6.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text Task Upgrade White [Tasks]?>Task Upgrade White [Tasks]</xref> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Print the PQT-White via SDS task [D] 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">see: 
<xref keyref="TaskD" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-52469F28-548D-4071-A141-3BF8C5A6979C.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text Task [D] Print Quality Verification [Tasks]?>Task [D] Print Quality Verification [Tasks]</xref> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Judge the quality accordingly 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-831E3936-68A6-40A0-8CBF-A9BC161D4E54" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Install the additional license</title><p class="- topic/p ">In case of an upgrade with white, use the procedure: 
<xref keyref="Howtoexupgdowglicense" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-C979FE3E-043B-4B97-A44D-D4C6498A0E34.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text How to execute an upgrade, downgrade change of a license?>How to execute an upgrade, downgrade change of a license</xref>
